"script": "The acid in your stomach is strong enough to dissolve a razor blade, so why doesn't it eat through you? You see, your stomach pumps out hydrochloric acid so powerful it would burn a hole in wood, all to break down food and kill swallowed bacteria. But your stomach shields itself with a thick layer of slimy mucus the acid can't penetrate. And this lining rebuilds constantly, replacing itself completely every few days. But if that mucus ever wears thin, the acid touches raw flesh, and the result is a burning ulcer. So you're carrying a vat of poison held back by nothing but slime.",
